Both edits are correct. Here's a summary of exactly what was added and why each decision was made:

---

### What was added

**Handler function** (`common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3`, lines 1519–1541):

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt            = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format            = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```

**Detection entry** in `common_chat_try_specialized_template` (lines 1714–1723), placed last before `return std::nullopt;`:

```cpp
if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v0.3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
}
```

---

### Design decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl` for prompt building | The Jinja template already implements the full format (system prepend, `[INST]/[/INST]` wrapping, `</s>` after assistant); there is no need to rebuild it manually. |
| `p.literal(generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest())` | Mistral Instruct v0.3 has no tool-call tokens or reasoning markers in the *generated* output, so a plain content-capture parser is both correct and minimal. |
| `supports_thinking = false` | No `<think>` / `[THINK]` blocks in this format. |
| No `preserved_tokens` | `[INST]`/`[/INST]` only appear in the *prompt* context, never in the model's generated response, so there is nothing to preserve. |
| Detection uses `[INST]` + `[/INST]` + absence of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` | The Ministral 3 handler already requires `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` to be present; excluding it here creates a clean, non-overlapping partition. |
| Check placed after GigaChatV3, before `return std::nullopt` | The `[INST]` marker is common enough that placing the check last (before the fallback) minimises the risk of false-positive matches with future handlers. |
| No existing code modified | Per the stated constraint — only new code was added. |

